    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, so you're saying there's basically no valid argument for religious exemptions? if a group truly believes something is a matter of eternal salvation or fundamental morality, isn't it kind of dismissive to just say \"the state is more important\"? doesn't that just mean the state gets to decide which religions are \"allowed\" to exist in public life?",
